Iman Taleb Assignment 4: Bank EDA

Plot 1 Job vs Duration cateogorized by Marital status

ggplot(bank,aes(x = job,y = duration,colour = marital))+geom_point()

Plot 2 Days since previous campaign by age (curves for education)

ggplot(bank)+
  geom_point(aes(x=age,y=pdays))+
  geom_smooth(data=dplyr::filter(bank,education=="primary"),
              aes(x=age,y=pdays),color="blue")+
  geom_smooth(data=dplyr::filter(bank,education=="secondary"),
              aes(x=age,y=pdays),color="green")+
  geom_smooth(data=dplyr::filter(bank,education=="tertiary"),
              aes(x=age,y=pdays),color="red")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'

Plot 3 Frequency of ages against contact type

ggplot(bank)+geom_bar(mapping=aes(x=age,fill=contact))

Plot 4 Contacts done before campaign per default status

ggplot(bank)+
  geom_point(aes(x=default,y=previous),size=3,alpha=0.2,colour="skyblue")

Plot 5 Scaled balance against job boxplot

ggplot(bank,aes(x=job,y=balance))+
  geom_boxplot()+
  scale_y_log10()
## Warning in self$trans$transform(x): NaNs produced
## Warning: Transformation introduced infinite values in continuous y-axis
## Warning: Removed 723 rows containing non-finite values (stat_boxplot).

Plot 6 Density of days of the month last contacted, colored by previous outcome

ggplot(bank,aes(day,fill=poutcome,alpha=0.1))+ 
  geom_density()

Plot 7 Histogram of age split by housing

ggplot(data=bank,mapping=aes(x=age,fill=housing))+
  geom_histogram(binwidth=5)

Plot 8 Grid of points for days since last campaign against contacts previously done, split in housing and loan held

ggplot(data=bank)+
geom_point(mapping=aes(x=pdays,y=previous),alpha=0.5)+
  facet_grid(loan~housing)

Plot 9 Jobs sorted by mean balance, colorised by outcome of current campaign

ggplot(data=bank,mapping=aes(x=reorder(job,balance,FUN=mean),
                             fill=y))+
  geom_bar()+
  coord_flip()+
  xlab("Job Sorted By Mean Balance\nTop=Highest")

Plot 10 Polar chart of age, colorised by contact type

ggplot(bank)+
  geom_bar(mapping=aes(x=age,fill=contact),position="fill")+
  coord_polar()
